<subSubSection pageId="50" pageNumber="51" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="50.[151,1437,151,1187]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1054,1079]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Etymology.</emphasis>
From the Latin adjective, 
<emphasis box="[628,743,1054,1079]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">fimbriatus</emphasis>
, meaning fringed, referring to the distinctive row of tiny hairs extending along the facial ridge. Similar hairs are present in other species, but they extend less than half way to the base of the antenna.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
